    <briefdescription>
<para>An <ref refid="classDali_1_1ComponentApplication" kindref="compound">ComponentApplication</ref> class object should be created by every component-based application that wishes to use <ref refid="namespaceDali" kindref="compound">Dali</ref>. </para>
    </briefdescription>
    <detaileddescription>
<para>Component application draw multiple UI applications based on frame components. component application can draw multiple UIs in one process.</para>
<para>It provides a means for initializing the resources required by the Dali::Core.</para>
<para>The <ref refid="classDali_1_1ComponentApplication" kindref="compound">ComponentApplication</ref> class emits several signals which the user can connect to. The user should not create any <ref refid="namespaceDali" kindref="compound">Dali</ref> objects in the main function and instead should connect to the Init signal of the <ref refid="classDali_1_1ComponentApplication" kindref="compound">ComponentApplication</ref> and create the <ref refid="namespaceDali" kindref="compound">Dali</ref> <ref refid="classDali_1_1Widget" kindref="compound">Widget</ref> object in the connected callback. </para>
    </detaileddescription>
